abstract: At least 15 million television viewers watched the House of Representatives vote to impeach President Donald Trump after a full day of rancorous debate.
snippet: At least 15 million television viewers watched the House of Representatives vote to impeach President Donald Trump after a full day of rancorous debate.
lead_paragraph: At least 15 million television viewers watched the House of Representatives vote to impeach President Donald Trump after a full day of rancorous debate.
headline_main: At Least 15 Million TV Viewers Watch Impeachment Vote
headline_print_headline: At Least 15 Million TV Viewers Watch Impeachment Vote

abstract: The United States began flying Mexican deportees deep into Mexico on Thursday, and senior U.S. and Guatemalan officials said Mexicans seeking U.S. refuge might be sent to the Central American nation, in a renewed effort to slash border crossings.
snippet: The United States began flying Mexican deportees deep into Mexico on Thursday, and senior U.S. and Guatemalan officials said Mexicans seeking U.S. refuge might be sent to the Central American nation, in a renewed effort to slash border crossings....
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON/MEXICO CITY — The United States began flying Mexican deportees deep into Mexico on Thursday, and senior U.S. and Guatemalan officials said Mexicans seeking U.S. refuge might be sent to the Central American nation, in a renewed effort to slash border crossings.
headline_main: U.S. Deports Mexicans Far From Border, May Send Others to Guatemala
headline_print_headline: U.S. Deports Mexicans Far From Border, May Send Others to Guatemala

abstract: The federal government is reporting a 2.7% increase in the nation’s homeless population driven by a spike in California, according to an annual count that took place in January 2019.
snippet: The federal government is reporting a 2.7% increase in the nation’s homeless population driven by a spike in California, according to an annual count that took place in January 2019.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The federal government is reporting a 2.7% increase in the nation’s homeless population driven by a spike in California, according to an annual count that took place in January 2019.
headline_main: HUD Reporting 2.7% Percent Uptick in Homeless Population
headline_print_headline: HUD Reporting 2.7% Percent Uptick in Homeless Population

abstract: Foxconn Technology Group, the world's largest electronics manufacturer, could still qualify for up to $3 billion in state tax credits in Wisconsin if it makes changes to its deal with the state to reflect current plans for a plant that's under construction, Gov. Tony Evers said Thursday.
snippet: Foxconn Technology Group, the world's largest electronics manufacturer, could still qualify for up to $3 billion in state tax credits in Wisconsin if it makes changes to its deal with the state to reflect current plans for a plant that's under con...
lead_paragraph: MADISON, Wis. — Foxconn Technology Group, the world's largest electronics manufacturer, could still qualify for up to $3 billion in state tax credits in Wisconsin if it makes changes to its deal with the state to reflect current plans for a plant that's under construction, Gov. Tony Evers said Thursday.
headline_main: Wisconsin Governor: Foxconn Could Still Qualify for Credits
headline_print_headline: Wisconsin Governor: Foxconn Could Still Qualify for Credits

abstract: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau said on Thursday that the U.S. government should not finalize a trade deal with China unless the pact also secured the release of two Canadians detained by Beijing.
snippet: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau said on Thursday that the U.S. government should not finalize a trade deal with China unless the pact also secured the release of two Canadians detained by Beijing.
lead_paragraph: OTTAWA — Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau said on Thursday that the U.S. government should not finalize a trade deal with China unless the pact also secured the release of two Canadians detained by Beijing.
headline_main: U.S. Should Not Finalize China Trade Deal Unless Detained Canadians Are Released: Trudeau
headline_print_headline: U.S. Should Not Finalize China Trade Deal Unless Detained Canadians Are Released: Trudeau

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives overwhelmingly approved a new North American trade deal on Thursday that includes tougher labor and automotive content rules but leaves $1.2 trillion in annual U.S.-Mexico-Canada trade flows largely unchanged.
snippet: The U.S. House of Representatives overwhelmingly approved a new North American trade deal on Thursday that includes tougher labor and automotive content rules but leaves $1.2 trillion in annual U.S.-Mexico-Canada trade flows largely unchanged.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House of Representatives overwhelmingly approved a new North American trade deal on Thursday that includes tougher labor and automotive content rules but leaves $1.2 trillion in annual U.S.-Mexico-Canada trade flows largely unchanged.
headline_main: U.S. House Passes New North American Trade Deal, Senate Timing Unclear

abstract: After the House voted to impeach President Trump, readers across the United States shared their hopes and fears for the country’s future.
snippet: After the House voted to impeach President Trump, readers across the United States shared their hopes and fears for the country’s future.
lead_paragraph: The United States watched the third president in its history be impeached on Wednesday, prompting a debate among Democrats over when to send charges to the Republican-led Senate.
